Often, the invasive adenocarcinoma co-exists with ductal or lobular carcinoma in situ.  It is the most common carcinoma affecting women. --2003_Named locations of, or within, the body.:Tiny deposits of calcium in the breast that cannot be felt but can be detected on a mammogram. Concepts.definition: Named locations of or within the body.
Tiny deposits of calcium in tissue.  In the breast they can be seen using mammography, and if found in clusters may be indicative of breast cancer.
